<subSubSection pageId="63" pageNumber="64" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1437,402,1291]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1086,1111]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Biology.</emphasis>
This species is known from one lowland, dry, scrubby site on the outskirts of 
<collectingRegion box="[1197,1305,1087,1111]" country="Nicaragua" name="Managua" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Managua</collectingRegion>
. Minor and major workers recruited to a ground bait, and minor and majors were collected in the vicinity of the bait using a Davis sifter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="63" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1437,402,1291]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1194,1219]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Comments</emphasis>
. The minor worker of this species has the habitus and sculpture of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilson" authorityYear="2003" box="[1129,1311,1194,1219]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harrisonfordi">
<emphasis box="[1129,1311,1194,1219]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">P. harrisonfordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Unlike 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilson" authorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harrisonfordi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">P. harrisonfordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and similar species, the major worker has most of the face smooth and shiny.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
